# Literature Review: Measuring the Impact of the Digital Economy in Developing Countries

## Introduction

The digital economy, driven by Information and Communication Technology (ICT), has become increasingly important in recent years. It has the potential to contribute significantly to the economic growth and
development of developing countries. This literature review aims to provide a comprehensive analysis
of the research findings related to measuring the impact of the digital economy in developing countries.
The review will synthesize the available evidence, identify knowledge gaps, and suggest potential future
research directions.

## Overview of the Digital Economy in Developing Countries

The digital economy is estimated to make up around 5% of global GDP and 3% of global employment
(Bukht & Heeks, 2017). This highlights the growing importance of the digital economy in the global
context. However, it is crucial to understand the specific impact of the digital economy in developing
countries, as they often face unique challenges and opportunities.

## Economic Implications of the Digital Economy

The digital economy has significant economic implications for developing countries. It has the potential
to drive economic growth, create employment opportunities, and enhance productivity. A systematic
literature review by Tremmel et al. (2017) on the economic burden of obesity found that the digital
economy can contribute to the overall GDP of a country.
Furthermore, the digital economy has the potential to improve healthcare outcomes in developing countries. For instance, mHealth behavior change communication interventions have been found to be effective
in improving health outcomes in developing countries (Gurman et al., 2012). This suggests that the digital
economy can have a positive impact on the healthcare sector in developing countries.

## Measurement of the Digital Economy

Accurately measuring the impact of the digital economy in developing countries is essential for policymakers and researchers. However, defining, conceptualizing, and measuring the digital economy is a
